t\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"http://worpit.com/?p=1665\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:328:\"Worpit WordPress admin dashboard has been released! Worpit has been live and open to the public for 2 days but we&#8217;ve kept it quiet. Until now! Worpit is a new approach to WordPress system administration. And we know it will completely change how people manage their WordPress websites. Read on to find out how Worpit [...]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Worpit Admin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4962:\"<p></p><p><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1674 alignleft\" title=\"Worpit Logo W\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/worpit_w.png\" alt=\"Worpit Logo W\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" />Worpit WordPress admin dashboard has been released!</p>\n<p>Worpit has been live and open to the public for 2 days but we&#8217;ve kept it quiet. Until now!</p>\n<p>Worpit is a new approach to WordPress system administration.</p>\n<p>And we know it will completely change how people manage their WordPress websites.</p>\n<p>Read on to find out how Worpit can help you!</p>\n<p><span id=\"more-1665\"></span></p>\n<h2>So what is Worpit?</h2>\n<p>Imagine you manage 1 WordPress website. It&#8217;s easy&#8230; you log into the admin area and WordPress informs you there&#8217;s an update or two for your site.</p>\n<p>Perhaps it&#8217;s a plugin, or maybe it&#8217;s even the WordPress core. So you run the update and all is well with the world.</p>\n<p>Imagine now that you have 2 WordPress websites &#8211; you realise you have to head over to your other site and do exactly the same thing.</p>\n<p>Image now that you have 3, or 5, or 50, or hundreds.  It&#8217;s going to be a long day&#8230;</p>\n<p>Worpit is designed to solve this problem once and for all.</p>\n<p>By adding your websites to your Worpit admin dashboard, you can see at a glance all the updates available throughout your whole WordPress network of websites.</p>\n<p>Not only that, of course, you can run the updates on your sites that are required. You can update your plugins, 1, some or all of them.</p>\n<p>You can update your themes, all of them, or specific themes on specific sites.</p>\n<p>You can even update your WordPress core when WordPress.org release security updates, or new functionality.  And you can perform these updates in bulk, or on whichever sites you need, or on just 1 site.</p>\n<p>Worpit is flexible and powerful enough to let you decide what you want to do, without ever having to log into your WordPress sites to do the mundane task of running the update functions.</p>\n<h2>How can you get Worpit today?</h2>\n<p>Worpit is <strong>free</strong>.</p>\n<p>Anyone <a title=\"Worpit Sign Up\" href=\"http://worpit.com/worpit-sign-up/\">can get signed up to Worpit</a> and get started in a couple of minutes.</p>\n<p>We will ask you to confirm your account to prevent spam and fraud, and by the time your receive the Worpit welcome email, your account will be setup and you&#8217;ll be ready to rock!</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s free &#8211; so you have nothing to lose!</p>\n<h2>Is Worpit secure?</h2>\n<p>We built Worpit with security in mind. We delayed releasing the final product until we had implemented some of the best security around.</p>\n<p>Prevention is better than cure, and we take several precautions to ensure your data, your account, and your WordPress sites are secure:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Any and all sensitive account data stored by Worpit is 128bit-AES encrypted.</li>\n<li>Worpit does not handle, store, or receive <strong>any</strong> credit card or payment details: we <a title=\"Worpit Payment Gateway: WorldPay\" href=\"http://worpit.com/worpit-terms-of-service/worpit-payment-gateway-worldpay/\">offload this to WorldPay</a>.</li>\n<li>The Worpit WordPress plugin requires a unique identification key to be provided before a site is added to any Worpit account.</li>\n<li>After a site is added to Worpit, a secret PIN code is required before successfully connecting with the Worpit WordPress plugin</li>\n<li><strong>The Worpit WordPress plugin will <em>never</em> respond to any action request that originates from anywhere else except from worpitapp.com</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>The last point is very important and we believe we&#8217;re the only system of its kind to do this (but we could happily be wrong in this regard).</p>\n<p>We force every connection to &#8220;handshake&#8221; with <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">worpitapp.com</span> to verify that the request was valid, so there can be no spoofing of your plugin.</p>\n<h2>The Future for Worpit</h2>\n<p>Worpit v1.0 has a solid, reliable, and high performing foundation, and is set ready to change the way we manage our WordPress sites.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;ve lots of unique and exciting plans lined up and we want you to come along. Some of what we have planned include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a title=\"WordPress Backup &amp; Recovery: Instant, Automatic, Complete\" href=\"http://worpit.com/features/instant-wordpress-site-backup-recovery/\">WorpDrive &#8211; a revolutionary approach to WordPress backup/recovery</a>.</li>\n<li>WordPress installation and deployment tools &#8211; including templates.</li>\n<li>Advanced plugin/themes (including premium) management.</li>\n<li>White Labeling - so you can use Worpit branded for your company.</li>\n<li>much, much more&#8230;</li>\n</ul>\n<p>So why not get started with Worpit today and see experience the difference advanced WordPress admin can make to your online and professional life.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"http://worpit.com/2012/06/worpit-wordpress-admin-dashboard-released/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:50:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"LESS compiler now in Twitter Bootstrap plugin for WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:167:\"http://worpit.com/2012/04/less-compiler-twitter-bootstrap-plugin-wordpress/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=less-compiler-twitter-bootstrap-plugin-wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:84:\"http://worpit.com/2012/04/less-compiler-twitter-bootstrap-plugin-wordpress/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 25 Apr 2012 12:49:39 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"WordPress News and Updates\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"LESS compiler\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"WordPress plugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"WordPress Twitter Bootstrap\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"http://worpit.com/?p=891\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:139:\"LESS compiler is now available for Twitter Bootstrap plugin for WordPress for customizing the look and feel of your Twitter Bootstrap site.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Worpit Admin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7397:\"<p></p><p>Yesterday saw the release of Twitter Bootstrap version 2.0.3.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;ve been waiting for this release for quite a while as we&#8217;ve had a number of improvements in the pipeline.</p>\n<p>The biggest addition being probably the most important since the plugin was first released: a <strong>LESS compiler for Bootstrap</strong> within your WordPress site!</p>\n<h2>What is LESS and what does compiling mean?</h2>\n<p>You can think of LESS as &#8220;dynamic&#8221; CSS.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re at all familiar with Cascading Style Sheets (CSS) you&#8217;ll know there&#8217;s nothing dynamic about it. You define a style for an element and that&#8217;s that.</p>\n<p>If you want to also apply the same style given to one element to another element, you have to basically repeat the style.</p>\n<p>With LESS you have variables, functions and operations, making your styling much more&#8230; <em>dynamic.</em> You create a LESS &#8220;stylesheet&#8221; instead of a CSS stylesheet and compile it into CSS.</p>\n<p>It makes creating your CSS much quicker in the long run.</p>\n<p>The rest of this article outlines how to enable and use the LESS compiler within the WordPress Twitter Bootstrap plugin.</p>\n<p><span id=\"more-891\"></span></p>\n<h3>How does this relate to Twitter Bootstrap?</h3>\n<p>Twitter Bootstrap uses LESS to generate its CSS components.</p>\n<p>Up until now, the <a title=\"WordPress Twitter Bootstrap CSS plugin\" href=\"http://bit.ly/qRVL1i\">WordPress Twitter Bootstrap CSS plugin</a> allowed you to include the <em>original</em> CSS available from the Twitter Bootstrap site.  But there was no way to customize any of it to fit your theme.</p>\n<p>With version 2.0.3, now you can! We have included an interface that allows you to finely tune the main variables for your Twitter Bootstrap CSS.</p>\n<p>There is now a menu option within the plugin&#8217;s main menu to access the options available for customization.</p>\n<p>Most of the major Bootstrap LESS variables are included and for colours you are free to edit the text directly using variables and operations, or you can choose a colour directly using the <a title=\"JQuery Javascript Color Picker\" href=\"http://bit.ly/I8TP6g\" target=\"_blank\">colour picker provided</a>.</p>\n<p>Also kudos has to go out to <a title=\"LESSCPHP\" href=\"http://leafo.net/lessphp/\" target=\"_blank\">LESSCPHP</a> - a PHP-based LESS compiler library which we use to crunch the Bootstrap LESS.</p>\n<h2>How to enable the LESS compiler feature</h2>\n<p>By default, for the sake of some small performance gains the LESS compiler feature is not enabled by default.</p>\n<p>To enable the LESS Compiler feature of the plugin, follow the steps shown in the image below:</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_905\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\" style=\"width: 310px\"><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/how-to-enable-less-compiler.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-905 \" title=\"How To Enable LESS Compiler for WordPress Twitter Bootstrap plugin\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/how-to-enable-less-compiler-300x227.png\" alt=\"How To Enable LESS Compiler for WordPress Twitter Bootstrap plugin\" width=\"300\" height=\"227\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">How to enable the LESS compiler</p></div>\n<h2>Features of the LESS compiler for the Twitter Bootstrap plugin for WordPress</h2>\n<p>The LESS compiler feature of the plugin allows you to make full use of LESS variables, operations and mixins.</p>\n<h3>User input data validation</h3>\n<p>Since it is practically impossible to fully validate what you enter into the LESS fields we provided, we have done little in the way of validating correct LESS values.</p>\n<p>The following are important points to note about how the compiler validates data:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>For colour fields, if you enter a value that is a number between 3 ~ 6 digits long, we assume you are entering a hex value for the colour and treat it accordingly with or without the hash (&#8216;#&#8217;)</li>\n<li>For &#8216;size&#8217; fields, such a font size for example, if you enter a number we assume you mean pixels (&#8216;px&#8217;) and treat it accordingly. If you want, you can specify &#8216;em&#8217; or &#8216;pt&#8217;.</li>\n<li>You can reset all fields to default &#8211; this will run the LESS compiler on default Twitter Bootstrap variables so your CSS result will be identical to the standard Bootstrap CSS values.</li>\n<li>Everything else goes! If you enter invalid data, the compilation will in all likelihood fail. So be careful.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>LESS Compiler Variables</h3>\n<p>Depending on the variable type, there were be slightly different interface options.</p>\n<p>Take a look at the image below and the explanation of each one that follows:</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_912\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\" style=\"width: 310px\"><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/less-compiler-options.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-912\" title=\"LESS Compiler Variable Options\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/less-compiler-options-300x130.png\" alt=\"LESS Compiler Variable Options\" width=\"300\" height=\"130\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">LESS Compiler Variable Options</p></div>\n<ol>\n<li>For colours you can select the colour you want directly using a colour picker widget.</li>\n<li>Again for colours, if you don&#8217;t want to use a standard hex colour, you can input LESS options directly if you check this box. Check the box will remove the colour picker and allow you to edit it directly.</li>\n<li>This is the text field for editing directly.</li>\n<li>For convenience we have provided the Twitter Bootstrap default value for this variable.</li>\n<li>For convenience we have provided the name of the LESS variable in this case so you can specify a value for it here, and refer to it later on.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Precedence of CSS includes</h3>\n<p>Consider the following scenarios for the inclusion of your Twitter Bootstrap CSS library in your website:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>If you have enabled the LESS compiler and run a successful compilation, your website will <em>always</em> include your custom LESS-compiled CSS file.</li>\n<li>If you have enabled the LESS compiler and <strong>not</strong> run a successful compilation or the compiled file has been removed, your website will default to the standard Twitter Bootstrap CSS.</li>\n<li>If LESS compiler option is disabled, regardless of previous successful compilations, your website will default to the standard Twitter Bootstrap CSS.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Download LESS Compiled CSS file</h3>\n<p>You will know if you have a compiled CSS file on your site if the black button on the LESS compiler page is enabled.</p>\n<p>With this button, you can download the CSS file to your computer to review it. Right-click and &#8216;Save as&#8230;&#8217; to download the file.</p>\n<h2>Get the WordPress Twitter Bootstrap plugin today!</h2>\n<p>For more information and documentation on the plugin, please see the <a title=\"WordPress Twitter Bootstrap CSS Plugin Home\" href=\"http://worpit.com/wordpress-twitter-bootstrap-css-plugin-home/\">plugin home page here</a>.</p>\n<p>If you want to see more details of the plugin and download it, you can grab it from the <a title=\"WordPress.org repository for WordPress Twitter Bootstrap CSS plugin\" href=\"http://bit.ly/qRVL1i\" target=\"_blank\">WordPress.org repository</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:80:\"http://worpit.com/2012/04/less-compiler-twitter-bootstrap-plugin-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:4:\"href\";s:23:\"http://worpit.com/feed/\";s:3:\"rel\";s:4:\"self\";s:4:\"type\";s:19:\"application/rss+xml\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:44:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\";a:2:{s:12:\"upd